<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-07-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-07-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="400" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d400">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 815.00/1326.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé
                                    d’Affaires</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-07-25"><hi rend="italic">July 25,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 211.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that the period
                            of martial law, extended by presidential decree on May 19, was to-day
                            declared terminated by public proclamation as of date of July 20.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">J. Butler
                            Wright.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>